 of producing quasi-periodic signals in the same\nfrequency range as $p$-mode signals, despite being purely comprised of\nimpulsive signatures. Phenomena traditionally considered a consequence of wave\nbehaviour may be described by a number of high frequency but discrete nanoflare\nenergy events. This new physical interpretation presents a novel diagnostic\ncapability, by linking observed periodic signals to given nanoflare model\nconditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Oct 2020 18:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-26"}
